  <h3>X - Direct Long Falls</h3>

  <p><strong>Terrain:</strong> The terrain allows for longer falls that are "directly exposed" enough there is very little to no margin to recover from a loss in traction. A single mistake could easily lead to serious injury or death.</p>

  <p><strong>Psyche:</strong> Most people will be uncomfortable on this terrain regardless of it's simplicity or complexity, and even those that are comfortable being on it must take it seriously.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Class 1: Narrow but even ledges where a loss of traction would lead to a fatal drop.</li>
    <li>Class 2: Narrow uneven ledges, very steep slab, or a stairsteppy cliff face.</li>
    <li>Class 3-5: Climbing on a long ~vertical slope where a fall would be fatal.</li>
  </ul>

